CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 30, 1945, pg. 1, reads: "Glad To Be Back - T/4 John W. Turnipseed of Atlanta, Ga., was all smiles as he stepped off the big transport plane with the returning heroes at the County Airport, Monday. Glad to be back in America, he said he had no idea where he would be stationed in future. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Courier newspaper reporter George Brown, speaking to Sergeant John W. Turnipseed, with other soldiers deplaning from military transport plane in background, Allegheny County Airport
